race.comment: HOTCH POTCH (2) sets up nicely for this fourth-up where he will eat up the extra 100m. Expect him to drift back from his wide draw but with a genuine tempo anticipated, watch for him swooping. TOFINO (5) was a determined winner in a similar grade second-up. Not as effective in his last two but this looks easier and the Murtagh's booking adds confidence. NORMIE NO SHOW (1) never looked likely in town at the latest but his run prior was full of merit. Backs up quickly and won't be bothered by the added trip. HIT THE SLOPES (8) struggles to put two good performances together but backs up quickly and boasts strong peaks. Have to include.
